  "title": "Popliteal fossa",
  "body_html": "<div>The politeal fossa is a diamond shaped space at the back of the knee. <br /><ul><li>The floor is formed by the popliteal surface of the femur, the capsule of the knee joint and the oblique popliteal ligament and popliteus muscle fascia</li><li>It is bounded superiorly by Semitendinosus, Semimembranosus and Biceps Femoris  </li><li>It is bounded inferiorly by medial and lateral heads of gastrocnemius</li><li>It contains the terminal branches of the sciatic nerve (tibial & common peroneal nerves), popliteal vein and politeal artery (which lies deep to the vein)</li></ul><br /><i>Diagram illustrating popliteal fossa</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb308b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb308.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://www.tyckoart.com/Portfolio/popfossa.html'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb308b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb309b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb309.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://www.tyckoart.com/Portfolio/popfossa.html'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb309b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">3</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Lower limb</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\nThe politeal fossa is a diamond shaped space at the back of the knee. <br /><ul><li>The floor is formed by the popliteal surface of the femur, the capsule of the knee joint and the oblique popliteal ligament and popliteus muscle fascia</li><li>It is bounded superiorly by Semitendinosus, Semimembranosus and Biceps Femoris  </li><li>It is bounded inferiorly by medial and lateral heads of gastrocnemius</li><li>It contains the terminal branches of the sciatic nerve (tibial & common peroneal nerves), popliteal vein and politeal artery (which lies deep to the vein)</li></ul><br /><i>Diagram illustrating popliteal fossa</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb308b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb308.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://www.tyckoart.com/Portfolio/popfossa.html'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb308b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb309b.jpg'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb309.jpg'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://www.tyckoart.com/Portfolio/popfossa.html'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb309b.jpg'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div></div>\n\n\n<BR><BR><br><br></div>",
